'''''Andrew Harper's Hideaway Report''''' is a monthly [[newsletter]] that reviews [[luxury hotel]]s and [[resort]]s, typically smaller, more individual ventures.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ten Perfect Small Hideaways|url= http://www.huffingtonpost.com/andrew-harper/perfect-hideaways-with-10_b_3348656.html|work= The Huffington Post|accessdate =August 6, 2015}}</ref> The first issue appeared in 1979.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Top 20 International Small Hotels: Andrew Harper's Picks (Photos)|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/galleries/2013/09/07/top-20-international-small-hotels-andrew-harper-s-picks-photos.html|work=The Daily Beast|accessdate=August 6, 2015|author=Andrew Harper}}</ref> "Andrew Harper," a [[pseudonym]], was concerned about the influence of commercial considerations on [[travel]] [[review]]s, so he travels anonymously and pays his own expenses.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Checking In, Sir?|url = https://www.forbes.com/forbes-life-magazine/2004/0914/108.html|accessdate=August 6, 2015|work=Forbes}}</ref> Each year, the company conducts a [[opinion poll|survey]] of subscribers' favorite small hotels.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Top 20 International Small Hotels: Andrew Harper's Picks (Photos)|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/galleries/2013/09/07/top-20-international-small-hotels-andrew-harper-s-picks-photos.html|work=The Daily Beast|accessdate=August 6, 2015|author=Andrew Harper}}</ref> Andrew Harper, LLC employs 80 full-time staff with offices in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]], [[Chicago]], and [[New York City|New York]].{{citation needed|date=August 2015}} It also operates a luxury [[travel agency]].

