{{Infobox magazine | title = Electronic Products | logo = | logo_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_file = <!-- cover.jpg (omit the "file:" prefix) --> | image_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = <!-- up to |editor5= --> | editor_title = <!-- up to |editor_title5= --> | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = Trade magazine | frequency = Monthly | format = | circulation = | publisher = | paid_circulation = | unpaid_circulation = | circulation_year = | total_circulation = | founder = | founded = | firstdate = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | finaldate = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | finalnumber = | company = AspenCore Media ([[Arrow Electronics]]) | country = United States | based = | language = English | website = {{URL|http://www.electronicproducts.com}} | issn = | oclc = }} '''''Electronic Products''''' is an [[electronic component]] and [[technology]] [[trade magazine]] serving the electronic design community.
==History and profile== ''Electronic Products'' was founded in 1957.<ref name=had>{{cite news|title=Electronic Products Magazine|url=http://www.hearstadvantage.com/|accessdate=5 December 2015|work=Hearst Advantage}}</ref> The magazine was owned and published by [[Hearst Corporation|Hearst Business Media]] until February 2015 when Arrow Electronics acquired the magazine and publishes it under AspenCore Media.<ref>{{cite news|author=Bob Jones|title=Arrow buys Hearst’s technical media assets – who’ll buy UBM’s?|url=http://www.publitek.com/news/arrow-buys-hearsts-technical-media-assets-wholl-buy-ubms/|accessdate=19 June 2015|work=Publitek|date=18 February 2015}}</ref> Reaching over 120,000 electronic engineers (EEs) and others in the trade across the United States—in print and over twice that number online worldwide. ''Electronic Products'' is considered{{By whom|date=March 2014}} a leader in its category.
''Electronic Products''{{'s}} editorial sections provide information on new products from the smallest [[capacitor]] to the brightest [[light-emitting diode]] ([[LED]]). In addition, featured articles range from selecting the best components to fill an application need to the latest in developing electronics technology. The editorial content is rounded out with application-specific product sections and transcripts of discussion roundtables on subjects from [[military equipment|military]] to [[medical electronics]].
Since 1977 the magazine has offered the Product of the Year Awards.<ref>{{cite web|title=Electronic Products Magazine announces its 33rd Annual Product of the Year Awards |url=https://www.components.omron.com/components/web/pdflib.nsf/0/6DF43F022AEC6AF1862575470059D888/$file/HEG_POY_PressRelease_Final.pdf |work=Hearst Electronics Group |accessdate=19 June 2015 |date=6 January 2009 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
