'''José Ferreira Queimado''' (23 December 1913 – 23 December 2007) was the [[List of S.L. Benfica presidents|25th president]] of Portuguese sports club [[S.L. Benfica]].

Born in [[Olhalvo]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.zerozero.pt/director.php?id=237|title=José Ferreira Queimado|website=zerozero|language=Portuguese|access-date=28 April 2018}}</ref> Queimado served as president of Benfica on two occasions: between 17 June 1966 and 3 July 1967, and between 26 May 1977 and 29 May 1981.<ref name="presidents">{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/slb/historia/presidentes/|title=Presidentes: os nomes que marcam a história|date=15 March 2018|website=S.L. Benfica|language=Portuguese|trans-title=Presidents: the names that mark the history|access-date=26 April 2018}}</ref> During his second tenure, he inaugurated Benfica's swimming pool in 1978 and started the construction of the club's pavilion, named Pavilhão Borges Coutinho in honour of [[Duarte Borges Coutinho|his second predecessor]].<ref name="presidents"/><ref name="dn">{{cite news|date=24 December 2007|title=Ferreira Queimado morreu ontem|trans-title=Ferreira Queimado died yesterday|url=https://dn.sapo.pt/2007/12/24/desporto/ferreira_queimado_morreu_ontem.html|dead-url=yes|language=Portuguese|newspaper=Diário de Notícias|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071227230210/http://dn.sapo.pt/2007/12/24/desporto/ferreira_queimado_morreu_ontem.html|archive-date=27 December 2007|access-date=26 April 2018}}</ref> During Queimado's presidency, Benfica's [[association football|football]] team won two [[Primeira Liga]] titles ([[1967–68 Primeira Divisão|1966–67]], [[1980–81 Primeira Divisão|1980–81]]) and started to use foreign players in 1978.<ref name="presidents"/> For the services rendered to the club (as associate number 261), he was granted the rank of Merit Associate in 1970 and was awarded Águia de Ouro (Golden Eagle) by the club in 1980.<ref name="presidents"/><ref name="publico">{{cite news|date=24 December 2007|title=Morreu Ferreira Queimado, antigo presidente do Benfica|trans-title=Ferreira Queimado, former president of Benfica, has died|url=http://ultimahora.publico.clix.pt/noticia.aspx?id=1314779|dead-url=yes|language=Portuguese|newspaper=Público|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071225152508/http://ultimahora.publico.clix.pt/noticia.aspx?id=1314779|archive-date=24 December 2007|access-date=26 April 2018}}</ref> He died on his 94th birthday.<ref name="dn"/><ref name="publico"/>

