'''Kassim Basma''' (born in 1960 in [[Koidu|Koidu Town]], [[Sierra Leone]]) is a [[multimillionaire]] [[Sierra Leonean]] [[businessman]] and the second leading [[diamond]] [[exporter]] from Sierra Leone, accounting  for around 38% of all official Sierra Leone diamond [[exports]]. Basma was born in [[Kono District]] in Eastern Sierra Leone. He was born into a family of [[Lebanese people|Lebanese]] [[Cultural heritage|descent]] from the southern Lebanese village of [[Ain Baal]]. He is a member of the Basma family, one of the oldest families of Lebanese descent in [[Sierra Leone]].

