'''Kolbjørn Almlid''' (born 2 June 1945) is a Norwegian businessperson and politician for the [[Centre Party (Norway)|Centre Party]].

He hails from [[Verran]].<ref name=chair>{{cite news|title=Almlid overtar etter Brekk|work=Adresseavisen|language=Norwegian|date=11 November 2004|page=2}}</ref> From 1989 to 1990, during [[Syse's Cabinet]], he was appointed [[State Secretary (Norway)|State Secretary]] in the [[Norwegian Ministry of Petroleum and Energy|Ministry of Petroleum and Energy]]. He served as a deputy representative to the [[Parliament of Norway]] from [[Nord-Trøndelag]] during the term 1989&ndash;1993. From 1991 to 1995 he was county mayor of [[Nord-Trøndelag county municipality|Nord-Trøndelag]].<ref name=bio>{{stortingetbio|KAL}}</ref> Outside politics, he was a director in the [[Norwegian Industrial and Regional Development Fund]], later named [[Innovation Norway]] following a merger.<ref name=retire>{{cite news|title=Almlid flytter hjem|work=Adresseavisen|language=Norwegian|date=18 June 2005|page=20}}</ref>

Almlid has chaired the [[Central Norway Regional Health Authority]] from 2006 to 2012,<ref name=chair/><ref>{{cite news|title=Strøm-Erichsen vil starte på nytt i Helse Midt-Norge|agency=Norwegian News Agency|language=Norwegian|date=30 January 2012}}</ref> and [[Nord-Trøndelag Elektrisitetsverk]],<ref name=retire/> and was a board member of [[Vinmonopolet]] from 1998 to 2000.<ref name=bio/> In 2011 he became chair of [[Statnett]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Almlid ny styreleder i Statnett|agency=Norwegian News Agency|language=Norwegian|date=29 June 2011}}</ref>

