{{Orphan|date=July 2016}}
{{Infobox officeholder | name = Uchechukwu Sampson Ogah | image = UcheOgah.jpg | image_size = | caption = <!-- --> | | term_start1 = | term_end1 = | | successor1 = <!-- --> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1969|12|22}} | birth_place = [[Abia State]] | residence = [[Port Harcourt]] | death_place = | occupation = President/CEO, Master Energy Group | education = [[University of Nigeria Nsukka]], [[University of Lagos]], [[Institute of Management Technology, Enugu|Institute of Management Technology]] [[Enugu]], [[Ogun State University]] | religion = Christian | known_for = | website = {{URL|http://www.mastersenergyltd.com/}} }} '''Uchechukwu S. Ogah''' (born 22 December 1969) is a Nigerian oil magnate, entrepreneur, investor and philanthropist. Ogah is the President of Master Energy Group, <ref name="mastersenergyltd.com">{{cite web|url=http://w3.mastersenergyltd.com/news/president-masters-energy-group-businessworld-newspaper-man-year|title=Masters Energy - Welcome to our World|publisher=}}</ref> a conglomerate with over 15 subsidiaries and interests across a variety of industries. Ogah holds the Nigerian national honour, the Officer of the Order of the Niger (OON)<ref>[http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/the-2014-national-honours-list/190137/ "The 2014 National Award List"], ''ThisDayLive'', 29 September 2014</ref>
==Early life and education==
Ogah was born to Chief Wilson and Ezinne Pauline Ogah of Onuaku Uturu,Isuikwuato Local Government Area of [[Abia State]]. <ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.nigerianbiography.com/2016/07/biography-of-uchechukwu-sampson-ogah.html}}</ref>
Ogah attended Ishiagu High School, after which he worked at West African Examination Council (WAEC) from 1986–89, before he proceeded to the Institute of Management and Technology (IMT), [[Enugu State]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imt.edu.ng/|title=IMT, Enugu Official Website|publisher=}}</ref> where he obtained Upper Credit at Ordinary National Diploma (OND) in 1992 and Distinction at the Higher National Diploma (HND) Level in 1995 in Accounting. He also attended [[University of Nigeria]], Nsukka (UNN) where he obtained a Postgraduate Diploma in 2005. He also has a Bachelor of Science degree (Banking and Finance) from [[Ogun State University]] and a Masters in Business Administration (MBA) from [[University of Lagos]]. Ogah obtained his ACA in 2007. He is a Fellow, [[Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria]] (ICAN);<ref>{{cite web|url=http://icanig.org/ican/article.php?id=52|title=Membership|publisher=}}</ref> Fellow, Institute of Brand Management of Nigeria; Fellow, Nigerian Institute of Shipping; Fellow, Employment & Career and member, Chartered Institute of Bankers.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}
==Career==
Ogah began his career as a banker with a year of [[National Youth Service Corps|National Youth Service]] year at NAL Bank Plc. Thereafter, he took up full employment at All States Trust Bank where he worked for around two years before joining [[Zenith Bank]] in 1997. At Zenith Bank, he set a record of growing a new branch from zero balance sheets to over N9 billion and rose to the position of an Assistant General Manager (AGM) in [[Zenith Bank]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zenithbank.com/|title=Welcome to Zenith Bank|first=Zenith Bank Website|last=Team|publisher=}}</ref>
==Philanthropy: The Uche Ogah Foundation==
In December, 2001, Ogah established Uche Ogah Foundation which aims to provide empowerment, poverty alleviation, and providing education for the less privileged.<ref>[http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/uche-ogah-at-44-fire-in-the-minds-of-men/167071/ "Uche Ogah at 44: Fire in the Minds of Men"], ''ThisDayLive'', 22 December 2013</ref>
He had sponsored free medical services in different parts of Nigeria, in addition to building and equipping a number of modern hospitals in his native community, Uturu and other communities in Nigeria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.konnectafrica.net/uchechukwu-sampson-ogah-is-a-nigerian-star/|title=Uchechukwu Sampson Ogah is a Nigerian Star - Konnect Africa|date=4 July 2014|publisher=}}</ref> He also partnered with a number of medical centres, including the Hopeville Rehabilitation Centre, to fabricate artificial limbs and calipers for people with a disability.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://maristbrothersng.org/hope.php|title=Marist Brothers Nigeria|website=maristbrothersng.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-12-22}}</ref>
==Awards and recognition==
In 2014, Ogah was awarded, a national award - the Officer of the Order of the Niger (OON) by the Federal government of [[Nigeria]]{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}
His other awards and honours include: * Honorary Doctorate degree in Business Administration by [[Abia State University]]{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} * 2013 Nigerian – American Chamber of Commerce Outstanding Entrepreneur by Nigerian - American Chamber of Commerce{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} * Ambassador of Peace, UN-POLAC Effective Leadership Award by Global Youths Awareness & Development. Initiative (GYADI){{citation needed|date=May 2018}} * Award for Excellence Foundation Entrepreneurship Promoter of the Year by Entrepreneurship Promotions Academy Africa{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} * Episcopal Award for Faith Motivation by Bishop Isikwuato/Umunneochi, Anglican Corporate Excellence Award for Accomplishments in Private Sector Development by Institute of Management. & Technology, Enugu, (Aba Chapter) {{citation needed|date=May 2018}} * Diamond Father of the Year, 2012 by Catholic Men’s Organisation, Masters Dei Cathedral Parish, Umuahia.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}
==Professional membership==
Ogah's professional memberships include:
Fellow, Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria (ICAN) Fellow, Institute of Brand Management of Nigeria Fellow, Nigerian Institute of Shipping; Fellow, Employment & Career Member, Chartered Institute of Bankers Member, Governing Council of the Nigeria-Turkey Chamber of Commerce and Industry.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}
